http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Telangana-seeks-Rs.-1000-crore-aid-from-Centre/article13998659.ece

Irrigation and Marketing Minister T. Harish Rao on Wednesday met Union Agriculture Minister Radha Mohan Singh at New Delhi to hand over a letter written by Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao seeking a Rs. 1,000 crore assistance to construct godowns in a scientific way for storage of agricultural produce.The construction of 330 such godowns proposed to be taken up by the State government to store 17 lakh tonnes of produce would require Rs. 1,024 crore. Of this, the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development promised to provide a loan of Rs. 972.79 crore.